 the simulated 12-hour period (72 seconds), checking the environment every second.\n\n**Lighting Logic Applied:**\n- **Daytime (06:00 - 18:00):** Set brightness to **800 lumen** if the environment was dark and people were present or motion was detected.\n- **Nighttime (18:00 - 06:00):** Set brightness to **400 lumen** for general occupancy in the dark, and increased to **800 lumen** when motion was detected (indicating a desire to move/go somewhere).\n- **Sleep/Empty:** Set brightness to **0 lumen** when no motion was detected and no one was in the room, or during typical sleep hours without activity.\n\n**Summary of Actions:**\n- At **15:00**, lights were set to **800 lumen** (Day, Occupied).\n- At **02:00**, lights were turned **off** (Night, Empty).\n- At **19:30**, lights were set to **400 lumen** (Night, Occupied).\n- At **20:30**, lights were increased to **800 lumen** due to detected motion (Night, Moving).\n- At **22:00**, lights were turned **off** (Night, Empty).\n\nAll tool calls, including `change_lumen` and `sleep`, were logged as requested."]